@jupyter-kit/docs is licensed under the GNU General Public License,
version 2.0 or any later version, because the live WebR demo depends on
@jupyter-kit/executor-webr → webr → the R interpreter, which is
GPL-2.0-or-later.

The built documentation site ships that WebR integration as part of its
runtime, so the site as a whole inherits GPL-2.0-or-later.

A copy of GPL-2.0 is available at:
  https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/gpl-2.0.txt

GPL-3.0:
  https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt

If you want an Apache-2.0-licensed deliverable, drop the WebR demo + the
`@jupyter-kit/executor-webr` dependency. All other packages in this
monorepo (core, react, vue, wc, theme, math plugins, editor-codemirror,
executor-pyodide) are Apache-2.0.
